# Service Restart Check

After implementing, updating, or fixing anything, do a quick check and tell the user which services need to be restarted to pick up the changes.

## Checklist

At the end of your work, briefly report:

- **None** — If only docs, tests, or config that doesn't affect running services
- **API** — If `app/**` (Python) changed: `make run` (or `make run-local`)
- **Worker** — If `app/**` (Python) changed: `make run-worker` (or `make run-worker-dry-run`)
- **Frontend** — If `notion_pipeliner_ui/**` changed: `cd notion_pipeliner_ui && npm run dev`
- **Supabase** — If `supabase/migrations/**` changed: `make supabase-migrate` (or `make supabase-reset` for full reset)

## Mapping

| Changed area | Restart |
|--------------|---------|
| `app/**` (routes, services, domain, repos) | API + Worker |
| `notion_pipeliner_ui/**` | Frontend dev server |
| `supabase/migrations/**` | Run migration; no restart if DB-only |
| `requirements.txt`, `pyproject.toml` | API + Worker (after `make install`) |
| `notion_pipeliner_ui/package.json` | Frontend (after `npm install`) |
| Docs, tests, `.cursor/**` | None |

## Example

> **Services to restart:** API and Worker (`make run` and `make run-worker` in separate terminals) — backend code changed.
